bug.short_desc: "build" version has dependencies in broken order

long_desc.thetext:
When I build the source version of my app, the first three classes in the sorted order list are:
- qx.Bootstrap - qx.core.Environment - qx.Mixin
In the build version, it uses this order:
- qx.Bootstrap - qx.Mixin - qx.core.Environment
That breaks during loading the app because qx.Mixin contains this line:
__allowedKeys : qx.core.Environment.select("qx.debug",
but qx.core has not yet been defined.
I'll attach the complete source and build verbose outputs of the generator.
Derrell

Additional info:
Add #require(qx.core.Environment) to Mixin.js solves the problem.
Interestingly, adding #use(qx.core.Environment) does not.
Which trunk/master revision are you working with?

(In reply to comment #5) > That breaks during loading the app because qx.Mixin contains this line: > > __allowedKeys : qx.core.Environment.select("qx.debug", >
This is rather strange, as (a) the key "__allowedKeys" is not private-optimized (as is typically the case for the build version), and (b) the entire call to qx.core.Environment should be optimized away, given that "variants" optimization is on and qx.debug is set through the config (For the build job, it is typically set to false).
Please re-do the build output using "generate.py -v -w".

I'm using latest master as of last night: 6b1ae66. It had the same result, though, with the version I'd originally retrieved upon the switch-over from svn to git. The problem did NOT occur with the somewhat older (some number of weeks) version I'd been using before that, from svn.
It's reproducible with a vanilla gui skeleton and OPTIMIZE set to [].

The Class.tree() method was delivering the class tree with unconditionally applying variant optimization to it; this was flawing the 'build' version where 'variants' is off (this must be a regression in trunk as it works for 1.5.x); variant optimization is now a normal optimization in Class.optimize (as it should be), and Class.tree is always delivering a vanilla (ie. unmodified) class syntax tree; this should also reduce the amount of tree-* files in the cache.
With 9b2af52.
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
